      • parse

        Node parse(Token start)
        Generate a node that is part of the abstract syntax tree with knowledge of token start If a parse() return null, don't emit an error message. The parser that failed is supposed to handle error reporting. A call to parse should consume _all_ tokens required so that a the current token is the last _not_ used token. This is vital for the process.
        Parameters:
        start -
        Returns:
        a Node on success or null if parsing fail
